natural problem: Find the cross product of $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 4 \\ -5 \end{pmatrix}.$
natural solution: The cross product of $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 4 \\ -5 \end{pmatrix}$ is \[\begin{pmatrix} (-1)(-5) - (4)(2) \\ (2)(3) - (-5)(1) \\ (1)(4) - (3)(-1) \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\ 11 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}}.\]

and h2 : "\<forall> i. c i = cross_product a b ! i"
